Commercial Bank of Syria’s 1st-Half Profit Rises 18%, Sana Says

-- B y   L i n a   I b r a h i m
-- 
2011-08-09T10:50:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/commercial-bank-of-syria-s-1st-half-profit-rises-18-sana-says.html
Commercial Bank of  Syria , the
country’s biggest bank, saw an 18 percent profit increase in the
first half of 2011 compared with a year earlier, the official
 Syrian Arab News Agency  reported today.  The state-owned bank’s profit rose to 13 billion Syrian
pounds ($274 million), up from 11 billion pounds, the  news
agency  said, citing General Manager Douraid Dergham. The bank
attracted 362 billion pounds in deposits and lent 393 billion
pounds, Sana cited him as saying.  The bank continues to finance investment projects and
extends loans to traders, industrialists, investors and public
institutions, Dergham said.  Syria has been engulfed this year by protests in demand of
political reform.  To contact the reporter on this story:
